* Configuration Files:
- This directory houses the configuration files most important for the perfect[fn:subjective] working system. This directory can be put on github (or another service) and pulled/pushed as required.

- Just provide a symlink from the files in this directory to the appropriate files (ideally, this will be handled by a script).
- This allows the configuration to be handled from one location (and thus, is hopefully easier to run a backup/restore process with).
- The symlink command is: =ln -s <src> <dst>=
- Example: =cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/bashrc .bashrc=

** List of link files:
|---------------+----------------+---------------------------------------------------|
| Source:       | Destination:   | Command:                                          |
|---------------+----------------+---------------------------------------------------|
| aptitude-dir/ | ~/.aptitude/   | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/aptitude-dir/ .aptitude   |
| conkeror-dir/ | ~/.conkerorrc/ | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/conkeror-dir/ .conkerorrc |
| emacs-dir/    | ~/.emacs.d/    | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/emacs-dir/ .emacs.d       |
| irssi-dir/    | ~/.irssi/      | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/irssi-dir/ .irssi         |
| mutt-dir/     | ~/.mutt/       | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/mutt-dir/ .mutt           |
| ncmpcpp-dir/  | ~/.ncmpcpp/    | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/ncmpcpp-dir/ .ncmpcpp     |
| stumpwm-dir/  | ~/.stumpwm.d/  | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/stumpwm-dir/ .stumpwm.d   |
|---------------+----------------+---------------------------------------------------|
| bashrc        | ~/.bashrc      | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/bashrc .bashrc            |
| mpd.conf      | ~/.mpdconf     | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/mpd.conf .mpdconf         |
| muttrc        | ~/.muttrc      | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/muttrc .muttrc            |
| screenrc      | ~/.screenrc    | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/screenrc .screenrc        |
| stumpwmrc     | ~/.stumpwmrc   | cd; ln -s .conf-scripts/stumpwmrc .stumpwmrc      |
|---------------+----------------+---------------------------------------------------|

